# Enforce LF line endings for all text files on every platform.
#
# Without this, Windows checkouts get CRLF (default core.autocrlf=true on
# GitHub-hosted Windows runners), which corrupts snapshot tests that
# capture HCL source bytes verbatim (e.g. variable type expressions in
# pkg/config/load_test.go).
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit declarations for the file types we actually ship and test
# against. Belt-and-braces against future ambiguity.
*.go            text eol=lf
*.tf            text eol=lf
*.tofu          text eol=lf
*.tf.json       text eol=lf
*.tofu.json     text eol=lf
*.json          text eol=lf
*.yaml          text eol=lf
*.yml           text eol=lf
*.md            text eol=lf
*.sh            text eol=lf
Makefile        text eol=lf
*.mod           text eol=lf
*.sum           text eol=lf

# Lockfiles + generated content should stay byte-identical across hosts.
go.sum                  -diff
testdata/golden/**      -diff
